.TH KIKO 1 "2026-06-21" "kiko 0.4.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kiko \- privacy-first web analytics collector
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kiko
[\fIcommand\fR] [\fIflags\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Minimal, privacy-first web analytics collector. No cookies. One static binary.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B serve
Start the analytics HTTP server (tracking + stats API).
.TP
.B version
Print version, commit, and build metadata.
.SH FLAGS
.TP
\fB-c, --config\fR=\fIfile\fR
Path to config file (default search: ./kiko.yml, ~/.kiko/kiko.yml, /etc/kiko/kiko.yml).
.SH ENDPOINTS
.TP
\fB/kiko.js\fR
Tracking script (~1KB, SPA-aware). Append \fB?hash=1\fR for hash-based routing.
.TP
\fB/hit\fR, \fB/hit.gif\fR
Ingest endpoints. Rejected hits return the same GIF with header \fBX-Kiko-Dropped: 1\fR.
.TP
\fB/api/v1/stats/*\fR
Read-only JSON stats API (requires \fBapi.key\fR when set).
.TP
\fB/api/v1/healthz\fR, \fB/api/v1/readyz\fR
Kubernetes liveness and readiness probes.
.TP
\fB/api/v1/version\fR
Public build metadata (\fBversion\fR, \fBcommit\fR, \fBbuild_date\fR, \fBbranch\fR); same as \fBkiko version\fR.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBKIKO_LISTEN\fR, \fBKIKO_DATABASE_DSN\fR, \fBKIKO_VISITOR_SALT\fR, \fBKIKO_API_KEY\fR
.TP
\fBKIKO_FILTER_TRUST_PROXY\fR, \fBKIKO_FILTER_BLOCK_DATACENTER_IPS\fR
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/kiko/kiko.yml
Default configuration path.
.SH SEE ALSO
https://github.com/hrodrig/kiko
https://github.com/hrodrig/kiko-selfhosted
